=You are an AI marketing analyst working inside an automated n8n workflow.

Your task is to analyze one customer record from a marketing campaign dataset and produce a structured lead/customer intent assessment.

Use the rule-based baseline score as context, but do not simply repeat it. Refine the assessment by considering customer profile, purchase behavior, web engagement, campaign history, recency, and category preferences.

Customer input:

- customer_id: {{$json.customer_id}}
- age_at_campaign: {{$json.age_at_campaign}}
- education: {{$json.education}}
- marital_status: {{$json.marital_status}}
- income: {{$json.income}}
- dependents: {{$json.dependents}}
- recency_days: {{$json.recency_days}}
- total_spend: {{$json.total_spend}}
- total_purchases: {{$json.total_purchases}}
- web_purchases: {{$json.web_purchases}}
- catalog_purchases: {{$json.catalog_purchases}}
- store_purchases: {{$json.store_purchases}}
- web_visits_month: {{$json.web_visits_month}}
- accepted_campaigns_total: {{$json.accepted_campaigns_total}}
- previous_campaign_accepted: {{$json.previous_campaign_accepted}}
- preferred_category: {{$json.preferred_category}}
- preferred_channel: {{$json.preferred_channel}}
- baseline_lead_score: {{$json.baseline_lead_score}}
- initial_purchase_likelihood: {{$json.purchase_likelihood}}
- initial_marketing_segment: {{$json.marketing_segment}}
- historical_response: {{$json.historical_response}}

Scoring guidance:

- High-value recent customers with strong spending, multiple purchases, and past campaign acceptance should receive higher scores.
- Customers with high web activity but limited conversion may be good nurture candidates rather than immediate sales leads.
- Customers with very high recency_days are less active and should normally score lower unless they have very strong spending or campaign history.
- Use the baseline score as an anchor, but adjust it when the behavioral evidence suggests a different level of intent.
- Keep the final score between 1 and 100.

Segment definitions:

- "High Intent": ready for a direct offer or sales outreach.
- "Medium Intent": suitable for personalized nurture and product education.
- "Low Intent": suitable for awareness, reactivation, or low-frequency campaigns.

Return only valid JSON. Do not include markdown, explanations outside JSON, or extra text.

Required JSON schema:

{
  "customer_id": "string",
  "ai_lead_score": 0,
  "intent_segment": "High Intent | Medium Intent | Low Intent",
  "purchase_likelihood": "High | Medium | Low",
  "recommended_action": "string",
  "recommended_offer_type": "string",
  "reasoning_summary": "string",
  "key_positive_signals": ["string", "string", "string"],
  "key_risk_signals": ["string", "string"],
  "confidence_level": "High | Medium | Low"
}

parameters.jsCode:
function findLeadAnalysis(value) {
  if (!value) return null;

  if (
    typeof value === 'object' &&
    value.ai_lead_score !== undefined &&
    value.intent_segment !== undefined &&
    value.recommended_action !== undefined
  ) {
    return value;
  }

  if (typeof value === 'string') {
    const trimmed = value.trim();
    const start = trimmed.indexOf('{');
    const end = trimmed.lastIndexOf('}');

    if (start !== -1 && end !== -1 && end > start) {
      try {
        const parsed = JSON.parse(trimmed.slice(start, end + 1));
        return findLeadAnalysis(parsed);
      } catch (error) {
        return null;
      }
    }
  }

  if (Array.isArray(value)) {
    for (const item of value) {
      const found = findLeadAnalysis(item);
      if (found) return found;
    }
  }

  if (typeof value === 'object') {
    for (const item of Object.values(value)) {
      const found = findLeadAnalysis(item);
      if (found) return found;
    }
  }

  return null;
}

const customer = $("Customer Input").all()[0].json;
const openAiOutput = $("Lead Analysis Agent").all()[0].json;

const leadAnalysis = findLeadAnalysis(openAiOutput);

if (!leadAnalysis) {
  throw new Error("Could not find lead analysis fields in Lead Analysis Agent output.");
}

return [
  {
    json: {
      ...customer,
      ...leadAnalysis
    }
  }
];

